    {
      "id": "1ad4750c-f3ba-80cd-bb0d-e6f425ec1c1d",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Models using Logs consistently outperform models self-reported measures, with a combination of both actually achieving marginally better results (Accuracy around 70%). Depending on feature set, the best alorithm also differed, putting emphasis into performing model selection when using these machine learning approaches. ",
